Interface CatalogUIHandler

public interface CatalogUIHandler

Defines the interface for classes wishing to define thier own catalog query or query result components.

Method Detail

makeComponent

public javax.swing.JComponent makeComponent(QueryResult queryResult,
                                            QueryResultDisplay display)
Make and return a component for the given query result object. Note that a Catalog also implement QueryResult, so the returned component may actually display query parameters or query results, depending on the argument.
Parameters:
queryResult - the object, for which a user interface component is being generated
display - if the first argument is a Catalog, this object can be used to display the results of a query.
Returns:
a component displaying the queryResult object (which may be a Catalog), or null, in which case the default component will be used.
